{{Quote|''A sequel to Meat Grinder ＆ Thermal Treatment․ Survive high-velocity props thrown by a fellow player on unstable platforms․ Models ＆ textures by Chim-Cham‚ voice cameo by Legends․''}}

'''Trash Compactor''' is a survival [[:Category:Game worlds|game world]] created by Jordo. Users stand on unsteady platforms, hovering above a deadly trash compactor. One player controls a cannon, that fires bulk waste at the players and platforms, which can knock them over into the compactor.

Each game lasts three minutes, indicated by a countdown on the wall. Players who survive the onslaught for three minutes, win the game. The cannoneer wins if they defeat all of the players.

==Overview==
[[File:Trash_compactorgameplay.webp|thumb|left|The cannoneer launches a car at an unsuspecting player.]]
Trash Compactor was created as a sequel to Thermal Treatment, and Meat Grinder for VRChat's Spookality world jam in 2024. The world was initially created on September 26, 2024 and released publicly on October 15, 2024.

Similar to Thermal Treatment, players must survive a wave of projectiles being thrown at them, or the platforms keeping them alive. Players can jump to other platforms that are more stable, or out of harm's way. The game lasts for three minutes.

===The cannon===
[[File:Trash_compactorcannon.webp|thumb|right|A point-of-view screenshot of the cannoneer's position, and controls.]]
The cannon can be controlled in different directions, to aim projectiles at players. The cannon lobs a barrage of bulk garbage at the players. Trash is fired at random, but comes in different forms, such as:
* Tires
* Tables
* Vending machines
* Pianos
* Cars
* Shipping containers

==Trivia==
* Trash Compactor was one of ten winners, for VRChat's [[Spookality 2024]] [[Worlds|world]] jam, part of the "Fractured Realm" series of worlds showcased by VRChat.
* The predecessor for Trash Compactor were two previous worlds by Jordo, called ''[[Community:Thermal Treatment|Thermal Treatment]]'' and ''[[Community:Meat Grinder|Meat Grinder]]''.

